injury_note: Oct 22: Jackson (groin) is considered day-to-day, Dustin Dopirak of The Indianapolis Star reports.
Oct 7: Sharpe will miss at least six weeks with a left hamstring strain, Brett Siegel of ClutchPoints.com reports.
Oct 22: Antetokounmpo is probable for Wednesday's regular-season opener against the 76ers due to right patella tendinitis.
Oct 22: Embiid (knee) has been ruled out for Wednesday's regular-season opener against the Bucks and won't play in any games this week, Adam Aaronson of PhillyVoice.com reports.
Oct 22: Olynyk (back) has been ruled out for Wednesday's regular-season opener against the Cavaliers.
Oct 23: Williamson (illness) was not present at Wednesday's morning shootaround, Christian Clark of The New Orleans Times-Picayune reports.
